<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910424-0225</DOCNO><DOCID>910424-0225.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Adobe Systems Inc.:   Fiscal First-Quarter Profit   Rose 23% to $12.4 Million</HL><DATE>03/21/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   ADBE</CO><IN>SOFTWARE (SOF)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Adobe Systems Inc. said net income rose 23% in the fiscalfirst quarter to $12.4 million, or 55 cents a share, from$10.1 million, or 48 cents a share, a year ago.   Revenue for the period ended March 1 climbed 42% to $52.6million from $37.2 million.</LP><TEXT>   The Mountain View, Calif., software concern attributed theresults to an 80% gain in applications product sales from theyear-earlier period and a 27% rise in royalties from originalequipment manufacturers that license the company's products,one of which is a page-description language for computerprinters.</TEXT></DOC>